  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="KT356-kilavi">makaṭ pōkkiya cevilittāy uraittatu. </p>


        <p xml:lang="en">Told by the foster-mother, who had let the daughter go. </p>
      </div>

      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="KT356">
          <l> niḻalāṉ ṟavinta nīri lāriṭaik</l>
          <l> kaḻalōṉ kāppak kaṭukupu pōki</l>
          <l> yaṟucuṉai maruṅkiṉ maṟukupu venta</l>
          <l> vevvaṅ kaluḻi tavveṉak kuṭitti</l>
          <l> yāṅkuval lunaḷko ṟāṉē yēntiya</l>
          <l> cempoṟ puṉaikalat tamporik kalanta</l>
          <l> pālum palaveṉa vuṇṇāḷ</l>
          <l> kōlamai kuṟuntoṭit taḷiraṉ ṉōḷē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l rend="indent2">In a difficult place without water, devoid of shade,</l>
          <l rend="indent">going hastily under the protection of the man with anklets,</l>
          <l rend="indent">[and] drinking troublesome muddy water that is hot, <note place="foot"> Syntactically the ideophone modifies <term xml:lang="ta">kuṭukki </term>, the act of drinking, which causes an unpleasant sensation of heat, but this is difficult to render in a translation.  </note>
        </l>
        <l rend="indent2">evaporated in swirls  <note place="foot">Is <term xml:lang="ta"> maṟuku </term>, according to the TL used of the wind, to be understood literally, that is, does it refer to veils of vapour moved by the hot wind? </note>      from subsiding mountain pools</l>
      <l>– how is she capable [of that], she,</l>
      <l>[tender] as a sprout, with [well-]fitting tight bracelets in a row,</l>
      <l>who, saying “[too] much”, does not eat even milk</l>
      <l rend="indent2">mixed with nice <note place="foot">Is am here an adjective? Does it mean something like <term xml:lang="ta"> nal? </term>
      </note>  rice from a pot decorated with red gold,</l>
    <l rend="indent8">which she received? <note place="foot"> Or: "held [by me]". </note></l>


  </lg>
</div>
</body>
